{"type":"message","id":"dd6455eb","parentId":"3542feb5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:16:44.676Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to understand the request.\n\nUser message (untrusted metadata) is label \"openclaw-control-ui\", id \"openclaw-control-ui\". Not sure context: likely a UI element? The user asks in Chinese: \"如何切换当前大模型下的其它模型\" meaning \"How to switch to other models under the current large model?\" i.e., they want to know how to switch models.\n\nWe have system configuration: default_model=openrouter/openrouter/free. They want to switch to other models. Possibly need to use tool to change model override? There is mention of Model Aliases and session_status can set per-session model override (model=...). Also there is a tool \"session_status\" that can set per-session model override.\n\nBut also there is a tool \"exec\" perhaps to run openclaw gateway status? However switching model likely done via some configuration. In OpenClaw, you can change the model used by sending a \"model\" parameter to the session_status tool? Actually session_status can show status and optionally set per-session model override (model=default resets overrides). So to switch model, you may need to call session_status with a new model.\n\nThe user is likely using the control UI to switch models. The UI maybe expects a command. But as an assistant, we can explain how to switch models, perhaps by editing configuration or using a command.\n\nWe must consider the policies: provide safe answer, no disallowed content. This is normal instruction. We can respond with guidance.\n\nWe should check memory: maybe earlier steps recorded that the user wants to switch models.\n\nWe can use memory_search to see if any prior context about model switching. Let's do memory_search with query \"model switching\" or \"切换模型\".\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b6ddf8bed6ae4672afb33c82","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"切换模型","maxResults":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":13838,"output":850,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14688,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774070196006}}
